<p>	After years of fair-minded advocacy to change the repressive, outdated food truck laws in the City of New Orleans, the New Orleans Food Truck Coalition is in danger of losing to opponents of progress. </p>
	<p> You, the progressive-minded food lovers, are our greatest asset.  Like us, you believe that food trucks are an important part of the future of food in New Orleans.  You've come to our festivals and followed us on Twitter, but right now the New Orleans City Council doesn't even know you exist. </p>
<p> Please help us change that by taking action:</p>
